This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method to improve the performance of a popular random projection method for machine learning tasks. It may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves analyzing the effect of a specific data structure (SRHT) on a machine learning algorithm. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields often deal with high-dimensional data and may benefit from efficient dimensionality reduction techniques. Finally, it may also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed methods.
